{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 03 — Structural Alignment Quality Investigation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook characterises the RMSD distribution from the stratified alignment sample\n",
    "(300 clusters drawn across size bands, ~17K pairwise alignments onto the highest-resolution\n",
    "reference in each cluster).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goal:** decide an RMSD threshold to call an alignment "good enough" for water pooling.\n",
    "Entries failing the threshold will be excluded from their cluster (or used to split\n",
    "conformationally heterogeneous clusters in a later step).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Sample:** `alignment_sample_results.json` — 50 clusters per size band:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Size band | Clusters sampled |\n",
    "|-----------|------------------|\n",
    "| 4–6       | 50               |\n",
    "| 7–12      | 50               |\n",
    "| 13–25     | 50               |\n",
    "| 26–50     | 50               |\n",
    "| 51–200    | 50               |\n",
    "| 201+      | all (22)         |\n",
    "\n",
    "Alignments were computed with gemmi (C++ BLOSUM62 sequence alignment +\n",
    "Kabsch superposition on matched Cα atoms)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.image as mpimg\n",
    "\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, '../scripts')\n",
    "from cluster_filter import CONSERVATION_DIR\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(CONSERVATION_DIR / 'alignment_sample_results.json') as f:\n",
    "    sample = json.load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Clusters in sample: {len(sample)}')\n",
    "\n",
    "all_rmsds     = []\n",
    "all_n_aligned = []\n",
    "total_failed  = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "for cluster in sample:\n",
    "    total_failed += cluster['n_failed']\n",
    "    for pair in cluster['pairs']:\n",
    "        all_rmsds.append(pair['rmsd'])\n",
    "        all_n_aligned.append(pair['n_aligned'])\n",
    "\n",
    "rmsds     = np.array(all_rmsds)\n",
    "n_aligned = np.array(all_n_aligned)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Total pairwise alignments:  {len(rmsds):,}')\n",
    "print(f'Failed alignments:          {total_failed}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. RMSD percentile table"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print('RMSD distribution across 17,213 pairwise alignments')\n",
    "print(f'  Min:    {rmsds.min():.3f} Å')\n",
    "print(f'  Median: {np.median(rmsds):.2f} Å')\n",
    "print(f'  Mean:   {rmsds.mean():.2f} Å')\n",
    "print(f'  Max:    {rmsds.max():.2f} Å')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Percentiles:')\n",
    "print(f'  {\"Percentile\":>12}  {\"RMSD (Å)\":>10}')\n",
    "print(f'  {\"-\"*12}  {\"-\"*10}')\n",
    "for p in [50, 75, 84, 90, 95, 99, 99.5]:\n",
    "    print(f'  {p:>11.1f}  {np.percentile(rmsds, p):>10.2f}')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Fraction of alignments below RMSD threshold:')\n",
    "print(f'  {\"Threshold (Å)\":>14}  {\"% aligned\":>10}')\n",
    "print(f'  {\"-\"*14}  {\"-\"*10}')\n",
    "for t in [0.5, 1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 3.0, 5.0]:\n",
    "    print(f'  {t:>14.1f}  {(rmsds < t).mean()*100:>9.1f}%')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. RMSD distribution — histogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "img = mpimg.imread(CONSERVATION_DIR / 'alignment_rmsd_distribution.png')\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(13, 5))\n",
    "ax.imshow(img)\n",
    "ax.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Interpretation and suggested threshold\n",
    "\n",
    "The distribution is **strongly bimodal**:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **~95% of alignments fall below 3.0 Å** (mostly < 1 Å — rigid same-protein structures\n",
    "  that simply differ by crystal packing).\n",
    "- **~5% of alignments are outliers (3–26 Å RMSD)** — these are likely conformationally\n",
    "  heterogeneous entries in the same sequence family: apo vs. holo, domain-open vs. domain-closed,\n",
    "  or disordered loops that shift the whole superposition.\n",
    "\n",
    "The 95th–99th percentile jump (2.54 Å → 18.19 Å) is a clean bimodal break:\n",
    "everything above ~3 Å is in the outlier tail with no dense population between 3–18 Å.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Suggested threshold: 3.0 Å RMSD.**\n",
    "\n",
    "Entries above this threshold will be excluded from water pooling for their cluster.\n",
    "If a large fraction of a cluster exceeds it, we may want to split the cluster by\n",
    "structural sub-family (a later decision).\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**Please visually inspect the representative pairs below in PyMOL / ChimeraX** to confirm\n",
    "that the threshold looks right. The pairs were chosen as the closest available example\n",
    "to each landmark RMSD value."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Representative pairs for visual inspection"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "target_rmsds = [0.50, 1.50, 3.00, 6.00, 20.00]\n",
    "labels = [\n",
    "    'Excellent (below any reasonable threshold)',\n",
    "    'Good (well within 3 Å threshold)',\n",
    "    'Borderline (~95th percentile, at suggested threshold)',\n",
    "    'Outlier (above threshold, likely conformational change)',\n",
    "    'Extreme outlier (near-random superposition)',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "reps = []\n",
    "for target in target_rmsds:\n",
    "    best = None\n",
    "    best_diff = float('inf')\n",
    "    for cluster in sample:\n",
    "        ref = cluster['reference_pdb']\n",
    "        for pair in cluster['pairs']:\n",
    "            diff = abs(pair['rmsd'] - target)\n",
    "            if diff < best_diff:\n",
    "                best_diff = diff\n",
    "                best = (pair['pdb_id'], ref, pair['rmsd'], pair['n_aligned'])\n",
    "    reps.append(best)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Representative pairs for visual inspection (target RMSD → closest example)')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f'{\"Target Å\":>8}  {\"Actual Å\":>8}  {\"Query\":>6}  {\"Reference\":>9}  {\"N_aligned\":>9}  Label')\n",
    "print('-' * 90)\n",
    "for (target, label, rep) in zip(target_rmsds, labels, reps):\n",
    "    query, ref, rmsd, na = rep\n",
    "    print(f'{target:>8.2f}  {rmsd:>8.2f}  {query:>6}  {ref:>9}  {na:>9}  {label}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('To load a pair in PyMOL:')\n",
    "print('  fetch <query>; fetch <ref>; align <query>, <ref>')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Or in ChimeraX:')\n",
    "print('  open <query>; open <ref>; matchmaker #1 to #2')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Failure rate by cluster size\n",
    "\n",
    "Checking whether large clusters have a higher alignment failure rate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "size_bands = [(4, 6), (7, 12), (13, 25), (26, 50), (51, 200), (201, 10000)]\n",
    "labels_sz  = ['4–6', '7–12', '13–25', '26–50', '51–200', '201+']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'{\"Size band\":>10}  {\"Clusters\":>8}  {\"Pairs\":>8}  {\"Failed\":>7}  {\"Fail%\":>6}  {\"Median RMSD\":>11}  {\"% < 3.0 Å\":>10}')\n",
    "print('-' * 75)\n",
    "\n",
    "for (lo, hi), label in zip(size_bands, labels_sz):\n",
    "    band = [c for c in sample if lo <= c['cluster_size'] <= hi]\n",
    "    if not band:\n",
    "        continue\n",
    "    band_rmsds = [p['rmsd'] for c in band for p in c['pairs']]\n",
    "    band_failed = sum(c['n_failed'] for c in band)\n",
    "    band_total  = len(band_rmsds) + band_failed\n",
    "    r = np.array(band_rmsds)\n",
    "    fail_pct = band_failed / band_total * 100 if band_total else 0\n",
    "    med  = np.median(r) if len(r) else float('nan')\n",
    "    lt3  = (r < 3.0).mean() * 100 if len(r) else float('nan')\n",
    "    print(f'{label:>10}  {len(band):>8}  {len(band_rmsds):>8}  {band_failed:>7}  {fail_pct:>5.1f}%  {med:>11.2f}  {lt3:>9.1f}%')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. High-RMSD fraction per cluster\n",
    "\n",
    "How many clusters have a substantial fraction of high-RMSD entries?\n",
    "This informs whether we should simply drop outlier entries or split clusters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "THRESHOLD = 3.0\n",
    "\n",
    "high_fracs = []\n",
    "for cluster in sample:\n",
    "    rms = [p['rmsd'] for p in cluster['pairs']]\n",
    "    if rms:\n",
    "        high_fracs.append(np.mean([r >= THRESHOLD for r in rms]))\n",
    "\n",
    "high_fracs = np.array(high_fracs)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Fraction of cluster entries >= {THRESHOLD} Å RMSD (per cluster):')\n",
    "print(f'  Clusters with 0% high-RMSD:     {(high_fracs == 0).sum():>5} ({(high_fracs == 0).mean()*100:.0f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'  Clusters with <10% high-RMSD:   {(high_fracs < 0.10).sum():>5} ({(high_fracs < 0.10).mean()*100:.0f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'  Clusters with <25% high-RMSD:   {(high_fracs < 0.25).sum():>5} ({(high_fracs < 0.25).mean()*100:.0f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'  Clusters with >=25% high-RMSD:  {(high_fracs >= 0.25).sum():>5} ({(high_fracs >= 0.25).mean()*100:.0f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'  Clusters with >=50% high-RMSD:  {(high_fracs >= 0.50).sum():>5} ({(high_fracs >= 0.50).mean()*100:.0f}%)')\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print('Most clusters have only a small high-RMSD tail — simple per-entry exclusion is sufficient.')\n",
    "print('Clusters with >= 25% high-RMSD entries may warrant structural sub-clustering (future work).')"
   ]
  }
 ],
